          "date": "2015-04-09 14:36:28.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "subject": "LU-6431 obd: Do not block in !RUNNABLE state",
        "message": "LU-6431 obd: Do not block in !RUNNABLE state\n\n__l_wait_event() should only set !RUNNABLE state for a task\naround schedule functions, not around various callbacks\nthat could actually call into blocking codepaths and cause the\nstate to be lost.\nThis is seen from new kernel's CONFIG_DEBUG_ATOMIC_SLEEP logic.\n\nAdditionally get rid of unused __wsate variable and replace\nwaitq_wait/waitq_timedwait with schedule/schedule_timeout calls\nthere.\n\nChange-Id: I843b661711a2a516e37978431735132a0f1d7588\nSigned-off-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
